# Project Overview and Structure

This project is a web application built with [Next.js](mdc:https:/nextjs.org) and [TypeScript](mdc:https:/www.typescriptlang.org), using [Radix UI themes](mdc:https:/radix-ui.com/themes) for styling and components. It is set up to use [Contentlayer](mdc:https:/www.contentlayer.dev) for managing and rendering logs or content.

## Key Technologies
- **Next.js**: Handles routing, server-side rendering, and application structure. See [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts).
- **TypeScript**: Provides static typing for safer and more maintainable code. See [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json).
- **Radix UI Themes**: Used for consistent, accessible UI components and theming. Example usage in [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx).
- **Contentlayer**: Will be used for managing logs/content. (Configuration and usage will be in future files.)

## Project Structure
- `src/app/` — Main application code, including layout and pages.
- `public/` — Static assets.
- `next.config.ts` — Next.js configuration.
- `tsconfig.json` — TypeScript configuration.
- `.prettierrc`, `.prettierignore` — Code formatting rules.
- `.husky/` — Git hooks for code quality.

## Styling
- Global styles are imported in [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx).
- Radix UI's `<Theme>` component wraps the app for consistent theming.

## Adding Rules
- Store new rules in `.cursor/rules/` with a `.mdc` extension.
- Reference files using `[filename.ext](mdc:filename.ext)`.
